  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan: Supporting Access to Justice in Afghanistan (SAJA) - Phase III</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: Officials from the Ministry of Justice, the Attorney General&apos;s Office, the Ministry of Women&#x2019;s Affairs, the Afghanistan Legal Aid and Advocates Network and the Afghanistan Shelter Network.
Indirect beneficiaries: Afghan citizens.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to contribute to the effectiveness of criminal justice institutions in Afghanistan and their ability to protect Afghans from gender-based violence (GBV).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To support: 1) the Public Legal Awareness Unit of the Ministry of Justice (MOJ) to independently deliver legal awareness campaigns focused on GBV. 2) The Ministry of Women&#x2019;s Affairs (MOWA) to coordinate and deliver GBV advocacy and education campaigns. 3) Women leaders in the justice sector to competently and confidently support GBV awareness and policy advocacy. 4) The Family Response Unit, investigative prosecutors, and forensic science professionals to collect and preserve evidence in GBV cases while remaining sensitive to the needs of victims. 5) Partner professional training departments to independently deliver continuing professional development on GBV. 6) The Elimination of Violence Against Women (EVAW) Directorate and EVAW Courts to provide supplemental intradepartmental capacity development on GBV. 7) Partner justice institutions combating GBV to use databases to make policy and management decisions. 8) Partner institutions providing legal aid and women&#x2019;s protection centers to adhere to section-wide service delivery and practice standards. 9) Partner institutions providing legal aid and women&#x2019;s protection centers to utilize organizational strategies to manage and support their staff, members, and clients.</narrative>
  </description>
